	<p style="font-style:italics;">
	    Enterprise resource planning (ERP) integrates internal and external
	    management information across an entire organization, embracing
	    finance/accounting, manufacturing, sales and service, customer
	    relationship management, etc. ERP systems automate this activity with
	    an integrated software application. Its purpose is to facilitate the
	    flow of information between all business functions inside the
	    boundaries of the organization and manage the 
	    connections to outside stakeholders.
	    
	    <div style="font-style:italics;
